article.headline: James Madison 100, Siena 88
article.story: HARRISONBURG, Va. (AP) -- Juwann James had 20 points and James Madison shot 75 percent from the field in the second half in a 100-88 win over Siena on Friday night in the season opener for both teams. The Dukes (1-0) did not miss a shot in the final 11 minutes and led 71-70 with 9:17 remaining before using a 14-6 run to take control of the game. The Saints (0-1) took a 44-42 lead at halftime and led by as many as eight in the opening minutes of the second half before James Madison turned the game around. Siena was kept to 44.4 percent shooting for the game, including 35.5 percent in the second half. Pierre Curtis added 16 points for the Dukes, Abdulai Jalloh and Terrance Carter each had 15, and Kyle Swanston had 13. Edwin Ubiles led Siena with a career-high 27 points, and Ronald Moore and Kenny Hasbrouck each added 19.
